SIMPLE: carving
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carving
<hw>Carv"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of one
who carves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of decorative work cut in stone, wood, or
other material.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Carving</xex> in wood.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Temple.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The whole body of decorative sculpture of any kind
or epoch, or in any material; <as>as, the Italian <ex>carving</ex> of
the 15th century</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carvist</ent>⟦br⟧
